OL,3,CSenior police officer says use of stop
OL,4,Cand search is 'disproportionate'
OL,6,FThe Assistant Chief Constable of
OL,7,FThames Valley Police says the force is
OL,8,F"not going to mark its own homework"
OL,9,Fwhen it comes to the use of stop and
OL,10,Fsearch powers.
OL,12,FDennis Murray, said the current use of
OL,13,Fstop and search is "disproportionate",
OL,14,Faffecting trust and confidence in the
OL,15,Fpolice.
OL,17,FCurrently black people are up to five
OL,18,Ftimes more likely to be stop and
OL,19,Fsearched.
